<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/650548-hey-is-there-actual-m-m-romance-in">Hey! Is there actual &quot;M/M romance&quot; in this? Kissing, sex, love? Or is it just alluded to or fade to black kind of stuff? I want to read some queer fantasy books with legit romance that is as relevant as hetero romance.. :)</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_650548'><a id="like_count_community_question_650548" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/650548?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">2 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F452244.Lost_Souls">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/650548-hey-is-there-actual-m-m-romance-in">5 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/650548-hey-is-there-actual-m-m-romance-in">See all 3 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/53376961-bethany-ebert"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1626466755i/53376961._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/53376961-bethany-ebert">Bethany Ebert</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    I wouldn't call it "M/M romance" the way the book industry these days does M/M romance. It's a violent, harsh vampire novel with a lot of sex in it. M<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    I wouldn't call it "M/M romance" the way the book industry these days does M/M romance. It's a violent, harsh vampire novel with a lot of sex in it. Mostly gay sex. Mostly violent gay sex, sometimes incestuous, sometimes ending in death. It's great if you like twisted horror fiction, but if you're looking for "gay man meets gay vampire, sparks fly, they fall in love", you're looking in the wrong place.<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

